%N A061559 Array read by antidiagonals: T(k,d) = number of different hyperplanes in d-space with integer coefficients in set {-k,...,-1,0,1,...,k}.
%C A061559 The number of hyperplanes is T(k,d)=Sum(binomial(d,i)2^(d-i-1)(2*M(d+1-i,k)+M(d-i,k)),i=0..d-1) or T(k,d)=(1/2)*Sum(binomial(n,i)2^(n-i)M(n-i,k),i=0..n-1)-1, with n=d+1, where M(n,k) is the number of n-tuples (a,b,...) with 1<=a,b,...<=k and gcd(a,b,...)=1 T(1,d) is A029858 for n>=2.
